The paper proposes a novel neural network model for generating high resolution shallow depth-of-field images from a single all-in-focus image. The model involves depth prediction, lens blur, and guided upsampling modules, which are all differentiable and learned from data. The paper also discusses the datasets used for training and the effectiveness of the system and training strategies in experiments. Given the focus on image processing and computer vision techniques, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves graphics (cs.GR), multimedia (cs.MM), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques, which are all relevant to the proposed method.
